headline: Trump posthumously honors 'martyr' Charlie Kirk with the Presidential Medal of Freedom
description: Tuesday's ceremony coincided with what would have been Kirk’s 32nd birthday, just over a month after the right-wing activist was fatally shot while speaking to a crowd at Utah Valley University. Meanwhile, the US State Department said it had revoked visas of at least six foreign nationals who had 'celebrated the heinous assassination.'

headline: California plans on protecting minors and preventing self-destructive content by regulating AI
description: The legislation, signed on Monday by Democratic Governor Gavin Newsom, requires platforms to remind users that they are interacting with a chatbot − not a human − and to direct users to emergency services if they express suicidal thoughts.

headline: France's political crisis weakens French and European growth
